<a name="1333"></a><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td width=500><p><b>Re: Server Side Filtering: On Test</b> <font size=2>(Score: 1)<br>by Dumesh on Friday, March 23 @ 14:51:26 EST<br>(<a href="user.php?op=userinfo&uname=Dumesh">User Info</a>) </font></td></tr><tr><td>There has always been a packet of data that is sent every 6 seconds that updates health of you, your party, your target, and probably other Mobs in the immediate vicinity.  In addition to the updates every 6 seconds, everytime one of those targets takes damage, that creatures hp are updated by a packet of info.  Now, if you filter other hits, those intermediate updates will stop being sent.  You will only get updates on others health every 6 seconds; probably not a good idea for healers.  Hopefully the filters will be more precise than the current client side filters.</td></tr></table><br><p>[ No Comments Allowed for Anonymous, please <a href="user.php">register</a>  | <a href="comments.php?sid=162&pid=0&mode=&order=&thold=">Parent</a> ]</font><p></ul></p><a name="1335"></a><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td width=500><p><b>Re: Server Side Filtering: On Test</b> <font size=2>(Score: 0)<br>by Anonymous on Friday, March 23 @ 14:54:10 EST</font></td></tr><tr><td>It means you won't get a lot of the information, it'll be stopped on the server end and not send to you at all. You will however get hit point updates, there's just a delay, and they won't be incorporating the work around to the delay until after the initial implementation.<br>
<br>
Healing classes won't be able to use it at first it seems...<br>
</td></tr></table><br><p>[ No Comments Allowed for Anonymous, please <a href="user.php">register</a>  | <a href="comments.php?sid=162&pid=0&mode=&order=&thold=">Parent</a> ]</font><p></ul></p><a name="1336"></a><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td width=500><p><b>Explanation . . .</b> <font size=2>(Score: 1)<br>by Kithoo on Friday, March 23 @ 14:55:43 EST<br>(<a href="user.php?op=userinfo&uname=Kithoo">User Info</a>) </font></td></tr><tr><td>Basically as it stand now whenever anything happens you get the info at (whatever delay there is between you and EQ Servers) and when your computer recieves said data it performs client side prediction of MobX's hitpoints (I'm gonna use Trakanon, because he'll make alot of sense).<br>
<br>
Now this prediction can not do regeneration, which is why sometimes Trakanon can look like he's getting hit points back (This really only happened when he died the first few times and people weren't slamming him hard enough in the early goings.) That's because hit points are only updated every 6 seconds.  Every 6 seconds your computer is recieveing the hp of (and I'm guessing here) every mob in the zone . . . I'm not sure if its every mob in a radius or what, but I'm pretty sure its the WHOLE ZONE, which is why ShowEQ is so freaking effective.<br>
<br>
Well, now the problem is going to be if you filter out ALL that info you're only going to get HP info every 6 seconds . .  PERIOD.  Which, I think . . .  is going to lead to ALOT of clerics still leaving Other's Hits on.<br>
<br>
Its still a good move for EQ, and one of the first logical thing Verant has done in ages.  I haven't logged onto test and checked it out, so I can't really say how it REALLY works. . .  I can just translate what Absor told us.<br>
<br>
Kithoo -  I'm really not a mathmetician</td></tr></table><br><p>[ No Comments Allowed for Anonymous, please <a href="user.php">register</a>  | <a href="comments.php?sid=162&pid=0&mode=&order=&thold=">Parent</a> ]</font><p><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=1343&sid=162&pid=1336&mode=&order=&thold=#1343">I hope they think about this...</a> by Anonymous <font size=2>on Friday, March 23 @ 21:03:30 EST</font><br></ul></p><a name="1338"></a><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td width=500><p><b>Re: Server Side Filtering: On Test</b> <font size=2>(Score: 0)<br>by Anonymous on Friday, March 23 @ 15:51:31 EST</font></td></tr><tr><td>if they could set it so that you only recieve info for the mobs and your group then healers would still be good to go, its the AOEs that slam 40 raid members and that lag thats generated that kills your connection.<br>
